  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Knowingly processing criminal proceeds\n- Intent to disguise the origin of funds\n- Transactions designed to hide illegal sources of money\n\nSpecific details and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction. Would you like me to provide more nuanced information about money laundering laws?",
